            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>Thai green curry paste</strong> to the pan with the shallot and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>creamed coconut </strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, add your<strong> fish sauce</strong> along with your<strong> lime leaf[ves]</strong>, the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lime[s]</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>fragrant stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1598263102942-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1598263102942-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1598263102942-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1598263102942-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1598263102942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>haddock bites </strong>(unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!), <strong>chopped green beans</strong> and <strong>fragrant stock</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until the haddock is cooked through (your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily) and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>Thai green haddock curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Add an extra splash of water if the sauce thickens too quickly!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1598263113023-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1598263113023-x400.jpg",
